    <h2>CSS3 transitions and transforms</h2>

    <p>My teaching presentation on this topic is found in the link below.</p>
    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6gH24oXlf1U&feature=youtu.be">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6gH24oXlf1U&feature=youtu.be</a>

    <h4>This is a flashcard that uses both transition and transform</h4>
    <div id="flashcard">
        <div id="card_surface" class="shadow">
            <div class="front face">
                <p>What is the default subnet mask for a class C IP address?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="back face center">
                <p>255.255.255.0</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <style>
        #flashcard {
            position: relative;
            margin: 10px auto;
            width: 120px;
            height: 190px;
            z-index: 1;
        }
        #flashcard {
            perspective: 1000;
        }
        #card_surface {
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            transform-style: preserve-3d;
            /* this is what makes it look like it flips */
            transition: all 1.0s linear;
        }
        #flashcard:hover #card_surface {
            /* This makes it so the other side is displayed */
            transform: rotateY(180deg);
            box-shadow: -5px 5px 5px #aaa;
        }
        .face {
            position: absolute;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            backface-visibility: hidden;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            padding: 10px;
            color: black;
            text-align: center;
            background-color: #ddd;
        }
        .face.back {
            display: block;
            /* This makes it so the front is shown */
            transform: rotateY(180deg);
            box-sizing: border-box;
            padding: 10px;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            background-color: #aaa;
        }
    </style>

    <h4>This is a simple 10 second timer that uses transitions.</h4>

    <div id="timeleft"><div id="timer">Hover your mouse here to use the 10 second timer.</div></div>
    <style> 
        #timer {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            background: red;
            -webkit-transition: width 2s; /* For Safari 3.1 to 6.0 */
            
            transition: width 10s;
        }

        #timer:hover {
            width: 400px;
            transition-timing-function: linear; /* This makes the timer run evenly */
        }
        #timeleft {
            width: 400px;
            height: 100px;
            background: green;
        }
    </style>
<h4>This element is moved using a transform</h4>
<div id="transform">Hover here to see me tilt.</div>

<style>
#transform {
    width: 300px;
    height: 100px;
    border: 1px solid black;
}

#transform:hover {
    -ms-transform: rotate(20deg); /* IE 9 */
    -webkit-transform: rotate(20deg); /* Safari */
    transform: rotate(20deg); /* Standard syntax */
    
}
</style>
